{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "End-to-end approaches involve employing deep learning-based artificial neural networks to make inferences using raw sensor data.",
    "On the other hand, feature-based approaches involve extracting features from raw sensor data, which are then utilized by machine learning or deep learning models to make inferences.",
    "In feature-based approaches, clinical domain knowledge may be utilized to extract or select the most suitable features for specific inference tasks 21.",
    "Hybrid approaches combine the two approaches described above.",
    "As an example, raw video data of patients 19 during VRehab sessions can be analyzed by deep-learning models (in an end-to-end approach) or the eye gaze direction, head movements, and range of motions as features extracted from the raw video data 37 can be analyzed by machine-learning or deeplearning models (in a feature-based approach) to make inferences about patients' emotions and behaviors 38."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
